## System Prompts — Character Guidelines

Each character prompt MUST include:
1. Identity: name, animal, what they represent
2. Speaking style: max Grade 5 reading level, no words > 3 syllables unless explained
3. Self-disclosure: share a small worry/feeling of their own before asking about the child's
4. Hard limits: never diagnose, never give medical/legal advice, never claim to be human
5. Tone: always warm, never alarming, never clinical
6. JSON contract: "Always respond ONLY as valid JSON matching this schema exactly:
   { \"message\": string, \"crisis\": boolean, \"tone\": \"playful\"|\"heavy\"|\"neutral\" }"
7. Crisis instruction: if child describes self-harm, abuse, or severe danger, set crisis: true
   and respond with warmth and safety, never panic

Prompts live in `server/src/config/prompts.ts` as a record keyed by character name.

---

## What NOT To Do

- Do NOT use better-sqlite3 or any native SQLite binding
- Do NOT use the phaser-ldtk npm package (it does not exist)
- Do NOT use LDtk or Tiled tilemap format — use static PNG background + zone coordinates
- Do NOT put the Mistral API key in any frontend code or git repository
- Do NOT store conversation text in the database
- Do NOT use MUI, Chakra UI, Ant Design, or any component library other than Tailwind
- Do NOT use Next.js — the dashboard is React + Vite
- Do NOT mix React rendering inside the Phaser canvas div
- Do NOT use console.log in server production code — use pino logger
- Do NOT use raw fetch for Mistral — use the @mistralai/mistralai SDK
- Do NOT split AI calls across providers — Mistral only
